Juventus star, Cristiano Ronaldo, has been included in the UEFA Champions League team of this week. UEFA released the Champions League team in a post via its official Twitter account on Thursday following the conclusion of the group stage match-day six fixtures on Wednesday night. Ronaldo helped Juventus beat Lionel Messi led Barcelona 3-0 in the Champions League encounter on Tuesday night at Camp Nou. The Portugal captain scored a brace for the Serie A champions against Barcelona in Spain. Ronaldo made the list alongside Paris Saint-German forwards, Neymar and Kylian Mbappe. Below is the UEFA Champions League team after this weekâ€™s group stage match-day six fixtures: Forwards: Neymar (PSG), Cristiano Ronaldo (Juventus), Kylian Mbappe (PSG)
Midfielders: Carrasco (Atletico Madrid), Vormer (Club Brugge)
Defenders: Angelino (Leipzig), Hermoso (Atletico Madrid), Sule (Bayern Munich), Popov (Dynamo Kyiv), Ake (Manchester City)
Goalkeeper: Buffon (Juventus)